# Sneakers & Streetwear Sales Analysis â€“ Step by Step

This document explains the full process of the sales analysis with screenshots, from raw data to the final dashboard.

---

## Step 1: Raw Data
The dataset contained product sales information including product type, brand, gender, category, country, price, quantity, and payment mode.  
![Raw Data](https://github.com/alice662/sneakers-stwear-sales-analysis/blob/1131cb0d1a9fa7bd2141446d3b6c2d648187f37a/sneakers_stwear_raw.png)

---

## Step 2: Data Cleaning
The data was cleaned by removing duplicates, formatting columns, and preparing the dataset for pivot analysis.  
![Cleaned Data](https://github.com/alice662/sneakers-stwear-sales-analysis/blob/1131cb0d1a9fa7bd2141446d3b6c2d648187f37a/sneakers_stwear_clean.png)

---

## Step 3: Pivot Tables
Pivot tables were created to analyze monthly revenue, category mix, sales by gender, and revenue by payment method.  
![Pivot Tables](https://github.com/alice662/sneakers-stwear-sales-analysis/blob/1131cb0d1a9fa7bd2141446d3b6c2d648187f37a/pivot%20tables.png)

---

## Step 4: Dashboard
Finally, an interactive dashboard was built to summarize the findings.  
It shows revenue trends, product type and gender analysis, units sold by category, payment insights, and revenue mix.  
![Dashboard](https://github.com/alice662/sneakers-stwear-sales-analysis/blob/1131cb0d1a9fa7bd2141446d3b6c2d648187f37a/Dashboard.png)

